&quot;I hope you see those mistakes and the improvements that can be made.&quot;--You whould learn to phrase things better, or else you'll just seem like an overbearing hack. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ubanishedknight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Banished Knight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(9/25/02 10:09:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7228.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Mech heads</span><hr size=1>      I have to say that I somewhat agree with Yann on a certain level.  Spike, everything you said is true, but I think it's too much.  A big part of designing mecha (among other things) is to simply, &quot;Make it look cool.&quot;  I know it's not totally about that, but it is important.  I mean an artist SHOULD take all the things you said into consideration when designing a mech, but not so much that it completely changes your design.  Honestly, just speaking for myself, I wouldn't watch a mech anime or read a mech manga if the mecha looked all crappy and bland, but their parts made sense.  I'd be bored because I like to be visually stimulated.  In my opinion, all those little extras and such on the mech that don't do anything are alright because it does the simple job of making it look cool.  I think both of you are right to a certain extent.  But I don't think that Yann should be SO concerned about the functions of each piece of the mech. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/usadclown37.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sadclown37</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.angelfire.com/linux/coolstuff1/avatar.html" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle